1
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:40,088
(Peter Arnett)
You may hear the bombs now.

2
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:42,091
if you're still with us,
you can hear the bombs now.

3
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:45,377
They are hitting the centre of the city.

4
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:46,779
(second reporter)
Now we can hear explosions...

5
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:51,138
..off in the distance
to the west of central Baghdad.

6
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:53,336
Clearly l've never been there,...

7
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:57,208
..but this feels like
we're in the centre of hell.

8
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,933
(radio chatter)

9
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:24,813
(President Bush) The 28 countries...

10
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:26,333
..with forces in the Gulf area...

11
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:29,173
..have exhausted all reasonable efforts...

12
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:31,569
..to reach a peaceful resolution,...

13
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:32,979
..have no choice...

14
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:36,211
..but to drive Saddam
from Kuwait by force.

15
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:47,729
(lraqi spokesman)
A great battle has been initiated.

16
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:50,015
The mother of all battles.

17
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,374
(Bush) Our objectives...

18
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:53,735
..in the Persian Gulf are clear,...

19
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:55,970
..our goals defined.

20
00:01:56,060 --> 00:01:59,018
lraq must withdraw from Kuwait...

21
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:01,375
..completely, immediately,...

22
00:02:01,460 --> 00:02:03,291
..and without condition.

23
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:09,895
(Bush) The liberation of Kuwait...

24
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:11,777
..has now entered a final phase.

25
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:15,648
l have therefore directed
to use all forces available,...

26
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:17,571
..including ground forces,...

27
00:02:17,660 --> 00:02:20,538
..to eject the lraqi army from Kuwait.

28
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,697
(Peter Arnett)
At this point it seems inevitable...

29
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:26,248
..that the ground war is only hours away.

30
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:28,649
Peter Arnett, Baghdad.

31
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:41,569
Don't ever for one minute
underestimate the enemy,...

32
00:02:41,660 --> 00:02:43,537
..but remember, we're better soldiers.

33
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:48,057
We're fighting with better equipment,
we're better trained and a lot smarter.

34
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:51,689
Sleep deprivation.
Our soldiers been up 46, 48 hours,...

35
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:54,169
..so stay on top of 'em.
Maintain your intervals.

36
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:55,136
Any questions?

37
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,377
Let's have a little prayer.

38
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:00,530
Dear God, protect us...

39
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:03,657
..as we protect our country
we so dearly love.

40
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:07,699
Keep us safe that we'll all get home
to see our families and our children.

41
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:08,656
Amen.

42
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:10,048
Amen.

43
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:18,094
- Let's kill 'em all.
- (all) Hu-ah!

44
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:26,970
You all right, Boylar?

45
00:03:28,820 --> 00:03:30,617
Hell, yeah.

46
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:33,414
- Let's heat 'em up, Nat.
- See you in Baghdad.

47
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,292
Yes, sir.

48
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:37,291
(engines starting)

49
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:58,853
Battle-carry Sabot.

50
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,377
Sabot bullet coming up, sir.

51
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:08,659
- Sabot loaded.
- lndexed.

52
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:09,456
Crew report.

53
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,053
- Driver ready.
- Loader ready.

54
00:04:11,140 --> 00:04:13,529
Gunner ready to give Saddam
a new way to hurt.

55
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:14,496
- Hu-ah!
- Hu-ah!

56
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:15,490
Hu-ah.

57
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,094
All right, Boylar?

58
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:19,249
Roger that.

59
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:22,252
All Cougar elements, this is Cougar-6.
Report Red Con 1. Over.

60
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:30,976
All Sabre elements, this is Sabre-6.

61
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:31,936
Move out.

62
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:57,177
(radio chatter)

63
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:01,336
Sabre-6, this is Cougar-6.

64
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:02,773
No joy over here.

65
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,976
Permission to try an alternate route. Over.

66
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:08,177
Roger that, Cougar-6.
Work your way to phase line hammer.

67
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:10,728
- (Nat) No surprises. Copy?
- Roger that.

68
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:13,892
l'm taking up the right flank.
l'll get back to you. Out.

69
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:21,377
Contact. l see flashes, 3,500 metres, sir.

70
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:23,894
- All right.
- Hold on. They got no range.

71
00:05:27,980 --> 00:05:29,254
2,500 metres and closing, sir.

72
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:30,853
Ready to lase and blaze.

73
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:33,539
Contact, sir. He's in range.

74
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:35,929
- Come on, let me kill his ass.
- Fire!

75
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,215
On the way!

76
00:05:42,340 --> 00:05:43,329
Yeah! Yeah!

77
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:45,012
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

78
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:47,694
- Find me another target, Patella.
- Loaded!

79
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:49,452
- ldentified.
- Fire.

80
00:05:56,740 --> 00:05:57,331
Fire!

81
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,290
(Patella) Got him! We got him!

82
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:09,859
Sabre-6, Liberty-6.

83
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:11,896
We got enemy tangos retreating...

84
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:14,289
..vicinity grid 2-4-9er-8.

85
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,611
Your pursuit should intercept
their retreat, grid 7-6-5.

86
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,258
Roger that, Liberty-6.

87
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:22,331
- Troops!
- Troops!

88
00:06:41,140 --> 00:06:42,778
Cease fire! Cease fire!

89
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:51,813
(shouting in Arabic)

90
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,299
Come on! Come on!

91
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:57,739
Sabre-6, this is Cougar-6.

92
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:58,969
Go ahead, Cougar-6.

93
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:01,335
l have got mines. Repeat, mines.

94
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:03,058
l gotta get the fuck out of here.

95
00:07:03,140 --> 00:07:05,495
(Nat) Work your way to grid line Charlie.

96
00:07:05,580 --> 00:07:09,334
Cougar-6 to all Cougar elements.
Let's get the hell out of here.

97
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:14,576
(shouting in Arabic)

98
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:31,453
Whoa! What the...

99
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:33,252
Oh, shit!

100
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:35,410
All Sabre units, this is Sabre-6.

101
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:38,219
We just lost a tank.
Anybody see the shooter?

102
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,814
- l didn't see anything.
- Where they coming from?

103
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:43,692
Who the hell is shooting at us?

104
00:07:43,780 --> 00:07:45,213
Liberty-6, we got enemy tanks...

105
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,052
..retreating grid 7-6...

106
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:49,210
- Patella, that one of our tanks?
- Hard to tell.

107
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,528
Make it out, and fast!

108
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:54,500
Oh, shit! We're almost browning out.

109
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,059
Nat, what's happening?

110
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:59,018
Liberty-6, we got enemy tanks on our flank.
We have contact.

111
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,055
This is Cougar-6.

112
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:02,813
Enemy tangos at phase line delta. Over.

113
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,936
- Patella, find me a target.
- l think l got one, sir.

114
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:06,738
Do you or do you not have a target?

115
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:07,616
l think so!

116
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,769
Gunner, Sabot, tank.

117
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:09,815
ldentify! Up!

118
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:10,889
Fire!

119
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,453
He just fired, sir.

120
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:15,575
They're firing at us!

121
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:17,969
- Loader!
- Up, sir!

122
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:18,970
Fire!

123
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:23,454
Yeah! That's the one!

124
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,495
All right.

125
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,969
(radio) Sabre-6, we just lost Cougar-6.

126
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,051
- We got him.
- Sabre, you just lit up a friendly!

127
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,459
l heard you! We... what?

128
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:31,939
Oh, my God.

129
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:34,215
You just lit up Boylar, goddamn it!

130
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:36,894
(radio) Sabre-6, Nat, what's happening?

131
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,379
Patella, was that one of our tanks?

132
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,530
He fired, sir.

133
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,451
At us or at the T-72s?

134
00:08:42,540 --> 00:08:43,450
l don't know.

135
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:45,770
At us or at the T-72s?

136
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:46,975
l don't know!

137
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:49,016
(Patella) Oh, Jesus fucking Christ.

138
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:51,375
(radio) Colonel Serling, report status now.

139
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:52,859
(explosion)

140
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:55,498
They have range on us, sir.

141
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:57,571
Sir!

142
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,892
Oh, Christ, Colonel...

143
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:28,574
l gave the order to fire.

144
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:53,698
So with your thermal equipment,...

145
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:57,534
..confused by burning tanks
and smoke obscuring your visual lD,...

146
00:09:57,620 --> 00:10:01,977
..you couldn't tell the difference
between the T-54 and the Abrams.

147
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,891
l believe that, uh, we...

148
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:06,369
l should have known the difference,...

149
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:09,657
..even with the night scope.

150
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:11,776
lf we weren't under attack,...

151
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:16,729
But, under the circumstances,
there was no way to tell the difference.

152
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:20,973
Under the circumstances,...

153
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:23,369
..l suppose there was
no way to tell the difference, but...

154
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:25,178
There was no way to tell the difference.

155
00:10:25,260 --> 00:10:26,454
Thank you, Colonel.

156
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:28,619
That's all we need.

157
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:05,931
(Patella) We're almost browning out!

158
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:10,172
(Boylar) We got enemy tanks on our flank.
We have contact.

159
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,488
Aah!

160
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:13,172
We just lost Cougar-6!

161
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:15,410
You just lit up a friendly!

162
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,489
(knock on door)

163
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:17,569
Colonel Serling?

164
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:18,570
Yes.

165
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:21,015
You OK? Can l get you something?

166
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,374
Yes, l'm fine. Fine.

167
00:11:22,460 --> 00:11:25,418
Uh, yes, you can get me a cup of coffee.

168
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,728
You got it.

169
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:29,857
We missed you and Meredith
at Banacek's party last night.

170
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:32,374
l'm too old to dance with you youngsters.

171
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:35,133
Meredith's not,
so tell her to come without you next time.

172
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:37,211
Oh, OK. l will do just that...

173
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,210
..next time.

174
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:41,178
(telephone rings)

175
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,249
Colonel Serling.

176
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:45,332
- Hershberg in five. Coffee's coming.
- Thanks.

177
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:46,409
Yes.

178
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:52,173
Washington Post?

179
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:55,175
About?

180
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:58,573
Yes, l was there.

181
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:00,935
That's a matter of public record.

182
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:05,293
Well, thank you very much, Mr...

183
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:09,532
Gartner. Thank you, Mr Gartner,
but l have nothing to say.

184
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:10,609
No, sir.

185
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:12,929
No, sir!

186
00:12:14,420 --> 00:12:16,615
Well, l'll do just that.

187
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:17,815
Right.

188
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:25,289
Colonel Serling's here, sir.

189
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:26,335
Ban.

190
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:30,095
l'm not talking to you.
Won't even come to my anniversary party?

191
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:32,614
You and Sylvia have been together,
what, a month?

192
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:36,136
The way she danced with that marine,
it won't last another week.

193
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:38,131
lt may be my last anniversary party.

194
00:12:38,420 --> 00:12:39,853
Were you there for me?

195
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,578
What's up?

196
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:44,295
Hey, Nat.

197
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:46,132
l've got to talk to you.

198
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,335
How we holding, Ban?

199
00:12:47,420 --> 00:12:48,648
Running late, sir.

200
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:50,935
- May l run a few things by you, sir?
- Quickly.

201
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,055
Lieutenant Boylar's parents...

202
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:53,050
Boylar?

203
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:56,052
Tom Boylar. He died in Al Bathra.

204
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:57,619
He'd been with me a long time.

205
00:12:57,700 --> 00:13:00,498
- From Virginia, right?
- Roger that, sir.

206
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:02,730
His parents have written to me.
They're hearing rumours.

207
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:05,732
You know we can't discuss it.
You have to put them off.

208
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:08,050
- Yes, sir, but...
- Tell them he died in action.

209
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:11,735
- He's a hero. That's all they want to know.
- Roger, but it's notjust his parents.

210
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:12,935
We got a call...

211
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:14,931
..from the Washington Post.

212
00:13:15,020 --> 00:13:16,248
A reporter named Gartner.

213
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:17,773
A reporter called you about Al Bathra?

214
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:18,975
You didn't talk?

215
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:19,970
Of course not.

216
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:22,779
Nobody'll hang you out to dry.
l won't let 'em.

217
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:24,088
Did you listen to the tape, sir?

218
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,619
Colonel, the war's over.

219
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:29,613
You and l have been given
the great responsibility and privilege...

220
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,533
..of investigating combat medals
for our army.

221
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,770
ln other words, we've been passed over.

222
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,778
l prefer to think of it
as a second chance, Nat.

223
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,816
We understand each other?

224
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:40,855
Yes, sir.

225
00:13:40,940 --> 00:13:42,339
OK.

226
00:13:42,420 --> 00:13:46,777
The White House heard we're considering
the Medal of Honour for a chopper pilot...

227
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,373
..who saved some guys
on a downed Blackhawk.

228
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:51,338
- Naturally they want it for Veterans Day.
- Naturally.

229
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:54,332
Which is why
you're taking over the inquiry.

230
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:58,015
We've got the rescued soldiers
in there for debriefing.

231
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,339
Attention.

232
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:04,371
Morning. Take your seats.

233
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:05,575
Everything in order?

234
00:14:05,660 --> 00:14:10,097
- Just going over the sequence of events.
- Bring Colonel Serling up to speed.

235
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,090
Morning, sir.

236
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,454
Good to see you again.

237
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:14,815
Could we get a picture
of you and the survivors?

238
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,379
No, thank you.

239
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:18,735
- Keep me in the loop.
- Thank you, sir.

240
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,971
- Morning.
- Morning.

241
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:26,848
Doug Bruno, White House.
Do everything my way and we'll be fine.

242
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:28,814
Nat Serling.

243
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:31,368
l'll, uh, get out of your way.

244
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:34,575
- Major.
- Sir.

245
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:37,857
25 February,
these men were part of a refuelling convoy.

246
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:41,296
Their Blackhawk was shot down
by an SA-7 west of Al Kufan.

247
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:44,452
Five seconds after it locked on,
we were down.

248
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:48,215
- We didn't know what hit us.
- Our lines were surrounding them so fast,...

249
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,530
..we got caught in a pocket of resistance.

250
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:55,694
lraqi ground troops on the ridge above
kept them completely pinned down.

251
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:57,532
Did you discuss surrendering?

252
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:03,937
Yes, sir, we did.

253
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:06,215
We were all wounded one way or another.

254
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:09,337
We weren't trained
for that kind of situation, sir.

255
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:11,411
Don't have to make excuses to me.

256
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,899
Go on, Sam.

257
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,857
That's all we got so far, sir.

258
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:16,498
OK.

259
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:18,730
- Lieutenant Chelli.
- Yes, sir.

260
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:22,893
Well,
as if things weren't bad enough already,...

261
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:24,936
..one of their T-54s...

262
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:28,615
..joins the ragheads up on the ridge.

263
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,418
(tank engine)

264
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:36,174
lncoming! Get down!

265
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:43,011
That round
kills the medic, Relleno, Gerspach,...

266
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,773
..and, uh, Egan here lost his leg.

267
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,090
So we figure that's it. We're dead.

268
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,818
But then we hear it.

269
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:53,016
Nothing like the sound of an inbound Huey.

270
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:54,249
(helicopter)

271
00:15:58,260 --> 00:15:59,534
Yeah!

272
00:15:59,620 --> 00:16:00,496
Yeah!

273
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,211
(Serling) This Huey, did it take any fire?

274
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,335
Right off the bat.

275
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:10,254
But this time
when the Huey comes back, it returns fire.

276
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,978
Ground troops go for cover.

277
00:16:12,140 --> 00:16:14,370
Then the Huey circles back over the tank...

278
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:17,577
That's when
they threw something overboard.

279
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:22,415
- Threw something, or something fell off?
- l couldn't tell, but the tank blew.

280
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:24,894
Oh!

281
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:26,208
Yeah!

282
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,858
Man, did it ever blow!

283
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:32,372
We, uh, we never did see
what knocked the Huey down.

284
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:37,098
(explosion)

285
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:39,171
We couldn't see the crash.

286
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:43,010
That night we caught sporadic ground fire.

287
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:46,456
The Huey was down below,
between us and the enemy,...

288
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,576
..so they caught most of it.

289
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:51,094
Any communications
between you and them?

290
00:16:51,180 --> 00:16:53,489
No, sir. As l said, our radio was wasted.

291
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,889
Shouting just draws enemy fire.

292
00:16:55,980 --> 00:17:00,815
So the lraqis,
they start to close in on the Huey...

293
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:02,333
..under cover fire,...

294
00:17:02,420 --> 00:17:04,809
..and the Huey returns fire.

295
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:08,688
We figure it's all over,
and that's when we hear the rescue team.

296
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:10,213
Cobras, Hueys...

297
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:12,370
And a big-ass A-10 Thunderbolt.

298
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:17,136
l swear l never heard such a sweet sound.

299
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:19,176
But now the fuckers are...

300
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:21,819
l'm sorry, sir.

301
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:24,414
The lraqis are letting loose with all they got.

302
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:27,253
- You were right the first time.
- (laughter)

303
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:31,572
Plus the Huey crew is still banging away.

304
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:34,413
We load our wounded aboard,...

305
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:37,697
..and that's when
somebody decided to leave the dead.

306
00:17:37,780 --> 00:17:39,771
l guess it was the commander of the rescue.

307
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:40,770
Mm-hmm.

308
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,452
And this... Huey crew,...

309
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:46,419
.they, uh, they returned fire
all through the final rescue?

310
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,297
Yes, sir. l... l think so.

311
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:50,769
l couldn't see much, though.

312
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:51,770
l heard it.

313
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:55,330
Nothing else sounds like an M-16.
Not no A-K or M-60.

314
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:57,695
l heard it, too.

315
00:17:57,780 --> 00:18:02,808
The last thing we see is the Thunderbolt
dropping napalm on the downed choppers.

316
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,937
l don't know if it was Captain Walden...

317
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:08,409
..but that Huey...

318
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,819
..saved our lives.

319
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:14,939
lt sure sounds like it.

320
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:20,131
OK.

321
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:25,090
Thank you for your help.
l'll look over your statements.

322
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:26,329
Thank you, sir.

323
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:28,012
Thank you, Colonel.

324
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,169
That'll be all.

325
00:18:29,260 --> 00:18:31,171
- Got something for me?
- l do, sir.

326
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:34,013
Walden's 201 file. Evaluation reports.

327
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,853
You know l'm going to need
background on these guys.

328
00:18:36,940 --> 00:18:40,933
Make sure we don't have a wife-beater
or an illegal alien or gays.

329
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:42,339
That'll blow it.

330
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:44,570
About this Congressional Medal of Honour.

331
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:48,778
lt's not the Congressional Medal of Honour.
lt's just the Medal of Honour.

332
00:18:48,860 --> 00:18:49,975
Tell that to Congress.

333
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:52,096
lf Captain Walden wins this medal...

334
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:54,489
You don't win it. You, uh, receive it.

335
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:56,093
lt's not a contest.

336
00:18:56,180 --> 00:18:58,740
But that is perfect. That is why l'm here.

337
00:18:58,820 --> 00:19:01,857
l'm not here
to get down your throat, make you crazy,...

338
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:03,896
..take these facts and twist them.

339
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:07,768
l just want to get these nuances out
of your head and to get it straight from you.

340
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:10,215
- lt's a woman.
- You didn't know?

341
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:13,212
What did you think the hoopla was about?

342
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:16,098
Banacek's got information
on three of Walden's men.

343
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:20,378
- The crew chief we're still tracking.
- This is Captain Karen Emma Walden.

344
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:25,898
She's the first woman ever to be nominated
for a Medal of Honour for combat.

345
00:19:25,980 --> 00:19:27,299
l mean, this is gold.

346
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:28,733
lt's gold.

347
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:31,170
Unfortunately it's posthumous,...

348
00:19:31,260 --> 00:19:33,455
..but l've got her little daughter.

349
00:19:33,540 --> 00:19:35,974
l got the President of the United States.

350
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:38,255
lt's all set in the Rose Garden.

351
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:42,618
The President's going to lean down and
hang that ribbon round that pretty face.

352
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:46,818
There is not going to be
a dry eye from Nashua to Sacramento.

353
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,936
Excuse us.

354
00:19:55,780 --> 00:19:57,577
OK, it was 5 to 1,...

355
00:19:57,660 --> 00:19:59,412
..hook shot.

356
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,650
Me and her are cheerleaders.

357
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:05,016
- More mashed potatoes.
- (woman) Sorry, no more potatoes,...

358
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:07,739
..but how about some bread?

359
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:10,539
Aah!

360
00:20:10,620 --> 00:20:12,258
(Boylar) Aah!

361
00:20:12,340 --> 00:20:14,900
Daddy, can l have your mashed potatoes?

362
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,574
Daddy?

363
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:20,616
Sir?

364
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:22,537
Can l have your mashed potatoes?

365
00:20:23,580 --> 00:20:25,491
M... Yeah. Sure.

366
00:20:25,580 --> 00:20:27,013
Yeah,...

367
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,579
..soldier.

368
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:29,775
You want 'em all?

369
00:20:29,860 --> 00:20:31,771
(telephone rings)

370
00:20:31,860 --> 00:20:33,009
That enough?

371
00:20:36,580 --> 00:20:37,490
More?

372
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:39,930
Hello?

373
00:20:40,020 --> 00:20:41,897
Yes.

374
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,175
Uh, who is calling, please?

375
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:45,579
Just a minute.

376
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:48,335
lt's for you.

377
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:49,330
Who is it?

378
00:20:49,420 --> 00:20:50,853
Somebody Gartner.

379
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:55,210
Want some more peas?

380
00:21:31,380 --> 00:21:32,495
Excuse me.

381
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:47,537
Where are you going?

382
00:21:47,620 --> 00:21:48,735
Fort Hood.

383
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:52,859
General Hershberg's got me investigating
a Medal of Honour.

384
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:54,817
lt's a woman.

385
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,413
Good for her.

386
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,569
Posthumous.

387
00:21:58,660 --> 00:22:00,810
Too bad, but still good for her.

388
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:04,016
Mmm. Too bad.

389
00:22:11,380 --> 00:22:14,736
You talk to the investigators today?

390
00:22:14,820 --> 00:22:15,809
Right.

391
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:20,011
lt's all right, isn't it, Nat?

392
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:22,779
Yeah. Fine.

393
00:22:26,340 --> 00:22:28,058
How long are you gone for?

394
00:22:28,140 --> 00:22:29,573
Couple of days.

395
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:35,336
Then why are you emptying
your sock drawer?

396
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:41,496
l may be gone more than a couple of days.

397
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:51,289
Nat.

398
00:22:51,380 --> 00:22:52,495
Yes.

399
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:56,096
l don't know what's happening.

400
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,772
Everything's fine.

401
00:22:59,020 --> 00:23:00,373
l'm handling it.

402
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:34,576
(Nat) Mr Rady,
you were Captain Walden's copilot.

403
00:23:34,660 --> 00:23:35,536
That's right.

404
00:23:35,620 --> 00:23:39,374
(Nat) Can you tell me
what you remember about Al Kufan?

405
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:50,539
l remember the earth.

406
00:23:52,340 --> 00:23:55,457
l remember... llario's face.

407
00:23:57,220 --> 00:23:59,017
l wish...

408
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:04,369
- She hadn't needed to be a hero so bad.
- That's not fair.

409
00:24:04,460 --> 00:24:06,690
We were just doing ourjob.

410
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:09,772
lt's not Ren's fault l got hit.

411
00:24:09,860 --> 00:24:13,614
She sure as hell saved the lives
of those guys on the Blackhawk.

412
00:24:14,540 --> 00:24:17,657
- You always defend her.
- Why didn't you like her?

413
00:24:17,740 --> 00:24:19,332
She was so butch.

414
00:24:19,420 --> 00:24:20,773
Honey, shut up.

415
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:24,452
She was, you know.

416
00:24:25,780 --> 00:24:28,692
One of those women
who want to be officers...

417
00:24:28,780 --> 00:24:30,611
Annie, shut up.

418
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:35,495
She gave her life for those men.

419
00:24:39,740 --> 00:24:41,059
She was a soldier.

420
00:24:56,820 --> 00:24:59,015
There she blows.

421
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:08,613
(gunfire)

422
00:25:10,420 --> 00:25:12,490
- We're taking fire!
- Holy shit!

423
00:25:18,620 --> 00:25:22,135
- Kill that motherfucker, Monfriez!
- l may as well be pissing on him.

424
00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:25,212
- We need a fucking air strike!
- We got no fucking bomb!

425
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:31,130
- Making another pass, Ren?
- Yep.

426
00:25:31,220 --> 00:25:34,417
No! We should go for altitude,
and call for support.

427
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,979
After we slow down that tank!

428
00:25:36,580 --> 00:25:39,538
- How we gonna do that?
- Shut up and listen, soldier!

429
00:25:39,620 --> 00:25:42,771
Altameyer,
unhook the aux fuel bladder port side.

430
00:25:42,860 --> 00:25:44,578
Get ready to push it overboard.

431
00:25:44,660 --> 00:25:45,979
Push it overboard, ma'am?

432
00:25:46,060 --> 00:25:48,016
llario, unhook the flare gun!

433
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:49,135
What the fuck...

434
00:25:49,220 --> 00:25:50,778
Do it!

435
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:52,816
lt's a bomb, asshole!

436
00:25:55,060 --> 00:25:56,539
Target coming up!

437
00:25:57,020 --> 00:25:58,009
Gimme more!

438
00:25:58,100 --> 00:25:59,294
Ready here!

439
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:01,415
- Got it?
- l got it!

440
00:26:04,140 --> 00:26:07,735
- Tell us when you're there! He'll kick it!
- Allow for the speed of the craft!

441
00:26:07,820 --> 00:26:10,653
- The pod will drop at the same velocity!
- He knows.

442
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:13,054
Pick your moment!

443
00:26:13,140 --> 00:26:13,936
Now!

444
00:26:21,060 --> 00:26:22,413
(cheering)

445
00:26:25,820 --> 00:26:27,811
Oh, my God!

446
00:26:30,420 --> 00:26:31,375
Oh!

447
00:26:32,780 --> 00:26:34,008
Whoa! Shit!

448
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:36,091
Whoa! Oh, God!

449
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:38,296
Hang on, llario! Grab ahold of me!

450
00:26:38,380 --> 00:26:39,779
Don't let go of me! Pull me in!

451
00:26:39,860 --> 00:26:42,977
Hang on.
Come on, llario! Pull yourself up!

452
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:44,698
Do something!

453
00:26:44,780 --> 00:26:48,056
No! No! Rady, call in a Mayday!

454
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:50,654
llario,... call it in!

455
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:55,098
(lario)
Mayday! Dustoff-3... we are going down!

456
