457
00:26:56,540 --> 00:26:58,735
We're going down! Mayday! Mayday!

458
00:26:58,820 --> 00:26:59,889
This is Dustoff-3!

459
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:01,891
We're going down! We're going down!

460
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:03,777
Mayday! Mayday! This is Dustoff-3!

461
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:04,770
We are going down!

462
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:08,250
Mayday! Mayday! This is Dustoff-3!
We're going down! We're going down!

463
00:27:08,340 --> 00:27:10,137
We're going down! Oh, my God...

464
00:27:22,580 --> 00:27:23,569
That's it.

465
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:28,816
l woke up three days later
on a hospital ship.

466
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:30,492
Nearly bought it, that's sure.

467
00:27:34,020 --> 00:27:37,979
(Larry King) When did you decide
the type of career in the Army you wanted?

468
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:42,372
(Schwarzkopf) That happened about
my third year at West Point when l was...

469
00:27:42,460 --> 00:27:44,849
l could have gone in the Air Force.

470
00:27:44,940 --> 00:27:46,817
l stood high enough in my class.

471
00:27:46,900 --> 00:27:50,654
You can't get away from that guy.
He's everywhere.

472
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:53,413
- Hell of a soldier, though.
- You think so?

473
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:54,899
l know so.

474
00:27:54,980 --> 00:27:56,413
Really. How?

475
00:27:56,500 --> 00:27:58,855
l was with him in the Gulf.

476
00:27:58,940 --> 00:27:59,850
No shit.

477
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:02,898
- Doing what?
- Armoured cavalry.

478
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:04,208
Hu-ah.

479
00:28:04,300 --> 00:28:05,938
Hu-ah.

480
00:28:06,020 --> 00:28:08,693
Once upon a time,
l was humping in the delta.

481
00:28:08,780 --> 00:28:10,736
- With who?
- The 9th.

482
00:28:10,820 --> 00:28:13,459
- You kicked some serious butt.
- That's right.

483
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:16,100
- One for my friend...
- Colonel Nat Serling.

484
00:28:16,180 --> 00:28:19,968
Make it a double for Colonel Serling.
Tony Gartner, Washington Post.

485
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:25,529
They won't find any criminal culpability
in the Al Bathra incident.

486
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,133
You got nothing to worry about.

487
00:28:27,220 --> 00:28:28,619
Those were my men.

488
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:30,850
l put that badly. l'm sorry.

489
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:34,569
Look, l went to Virginia
and spoke with Mr and Mrs Boylar.

490
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:38,014
You what?

491
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:42,059
l'm sorry, but they got a right
to know what happened to their son.

492
00:28:46,540 --> 00:28:47,689
l'll take that.

493
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:03,811
(steam hissing)

494
00:29:07,260 --> 00:29:12,493
(Serling) And this Huey crew, they, uh,
returned fire all through the final rescue?

495
00:29:12,580 --> 00:29:14,013
(Chelli) Yes, sir. l think so.

496
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:15,328
l couldn't see much.

497
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:18,059
(Thompson) l heard it.
Nothing else sounds like an M-16.

498
00:29:18,140 --> 00:29:19,209
Not no A-K or M-60.

499
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,733
(Egan) l heard it, too.

500
00:29:20,820 --> 00:29:24,335
(Chelli) Last thing we see
is the Thunderbolt dropping napalm...

501
00:29:24,420 --> 00:29:26,251
..on the two downed choppers.

502
00:29:30,020 --> 00:29:31,976
(screaming)

503
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:35,849
Oh!

504
00:30:19,340 --> 00:30:20,250
Sir!

505
00:30:23,540 --> 00:30:26,373
All right, this is antifungal cream,...

506
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:30,339
..but to kill the athlete's foot when
you're in the shower, just piss on your feet.

507
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:31,489
That's disgusting.

508
00:30:31,580 --> 00:30:33,616
What've you got for me today?

509
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:38,820
You want to get rid of the allergies to
bee pollen, then no caffeine, no chocolate.

510
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:41,460
Jesus. l give up coffee,
you can bury me now.

511
00:30:41,540 --> 00:30:43,337
(chuckles)

512
00:30:43,420 --> 00:30:46,890
- Morning, Colonel.
- Morning. You got some aspirins?

513
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:48,129
How many do you want?

514
00:30:48,220 --> 00:30:49,619
l take eight every day.

515
00:30:49,700 --> 00:30:50,576
Four's good.

516
00:30:50,660 --> 00:30:53,618
- l need to talk to you, Specialist.
