00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:58,296
l'm investigating the recommendation to
award a Medal of Honour to Captain Walden.

518
00:30:59,860 --> 00:31:00,770
Rowtero?

519
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,770
Yeah?

520
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,213
Can you cover for me?

521
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:05,734
l'm going to go feed the cancer genes.

522
00:31:05,820 --> 00:31:08,175
Do you really need to, uh, l mean...

523
00:31:13,220 --> 00:31:14,733
lt's fine.

524
00:31:14,820 --> 00:31:16,492
Uh, what do you want to know?

525
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:19,895
How long were you with Captain Walden?

526
00:31:19,980 --> 00:31:22,096
Um... over... over two years.

527
00:31:22,180 --> 00:31:23,533
Quite a long time.

528
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:24,689
Yeah.

529
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:25,815
You were her medic.

530
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:27,379
Yes, sir.

531
00:31:28,940 --> 00:31:30,453
l don't fly any more though.

532
00:31:32,540 --> 00:31:34,258
Well, don't miss it, do you?

533
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:35,250
Never.

534
00:31:35,340 --> 00:31:36,819
Never again.

535
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:38,458
That's quite a habit you got.

536
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:41,258
Yeah, it's, uh...

537
00:31:41,340 --> 00:31:43,854
..one of the few things l can call my own.

538
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:45,817
(laughs)

539
00:31:49,220 --> 00:31:50,209
So...

540
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:52,609
..tell me what happened at Al Kufan.

541
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:04,931
See, l'd, uh...

542
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:08,933
..l'd never been in... in combat.

543
00:32:13,380 --> 00:32:14,938
(tapping)

544
00:32:15,020 --> 00:32:16,772
(helicopter)

545
00:32:17,580 --> 00:32:19,536
Mayday! Mayday! This is Dustoff-3!

546
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:22,697
We're going down!
Mayday! This is Dustoff-3...

547
00:32:31,340 --> 00:32:33,331
(groaning)

548
00:32:37,940 --> 00:32:39,134
(moaning)

549
00:32:47,980 --> 00:32:48,890
llario?

550
00:32:48,980 --> 00:32:50,413
Yeah, l'm OK.

551
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:52,616
Rady's hurt.

552
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:54,133
Monfriez?

553
00:32:55,500 --> 00:32:56,376
(crackling)

554
00:32:56,460 --> 00:32:57,290
Altameyer?

555
00:32:57,420 --> 00:32:58,819
Functioning.

556
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:00,333
Fire in the hold!

557
00:33:06,060 --> 00:33:07,812
(lario) Come here, buddy.

558
00:33:10,580 --> 00:33:11,649
This is Dustoff-3.

559
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:12,536
Acknowledge.

560
00:33:12,620 --> 00:33:14,417
This is Dustoff-3.

561
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:15,410
Here. Come on.

562
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:16,899
This is Dustoff-3.

563
00:33:16,980 --> 00:33:18,049
Come on.

564
00:33:18,140 --> 00:33:20,859
Dustoff-3. Acknowledge.
Altameyer, how's that fire?

565
00:33:20,940 --> 00:33:23,215
Under control. Fuel tank's intact.

566
00:33:23,300 --> 00:33:24,653
(gunfire)

567
00:33:25,740 --> 00:33:26,650
Enemy at the back door!

568
00:33:26,740 --> 00:33:27,695
Come on! Come on!

569
00:33:27,780 --> 00:33:29,338
Monfriez, get that saw working!

570
00:33:29,420 --> 00:33:30,409
Come on! Get down!

571
00:33:35,860 --> 00:33:37,452
l've got the M-16!

572
00:33:37,540 --> 00:33:38,859
(gunfire)

573
00:33:38,940 --> 00:33:39,929
llario?

574
00:33:40,020 --> 00:33:41,214
He's bad. lt's the lung.

575
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:52,131
We gotta get him out of here.

576
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:55,773
- Head wound?
- Superficial. How's the radio?

577
00:33:55,860 --> 00:33:57,657
Dead. So's the ADT.

578
00:33:58,900 --> 00:34:00,777
Monfriez, easy on the ammo!

579
00:34:00,860 --> 00:34:02,293
We might be here a while!

580
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:03,409
Captain!

581
00:34:07,660 --> 00:34:10,458
You've seen me do this a million times.
You'll be fine.

582
00:34:11,780 --> 00:34:12,735
Ammo?

583
00:34:12,820 --> 00:34:15,175
l got this belt and three more boxes.

584
00:34:17,220 --> 00:34:20,929
OK, Altameyer,
rip out everything you can from the inside.

585
00:34:21,020 --> 00:34:22,578
We're gonna make a perimeter.

586
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:24,855
Monfriez, cover us!

587
00:34:24,940 --> 00:34:25,895
Go!

588
00:34:31,940 --> 00:34:33,931
Where's our Kevlar?

589
00:34:34,020 --> 00:34:35,009
l got one!

590
00:34:36,420 --> 00:34:37,569
Well, put it on!

591
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:45,333
Unh. How's he doing?

592
00:34:45,420 --> 00:34:46,694
He's the same.

593
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:48,133
l need a hook.

594
00:34:56,180 --> 00:34:57,818
As soon as it gets dark, we dig in.

595
00:34:57,900 --> 00:34:58,969
Then we wait.

596
00:34:59,060 --> 00:35:00,049
For what?

597
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:01,619
For the good guys.

598
00:35:02,140 --> 00:35:04,449
(laughing and shouting in Arabic)

599
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:08,651
You won't think it's so funny
when l nail your fucking ass!

600
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,816
Yeah, they were laughing.

601
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:17,935
You about, uh... You done?

602
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:20,813
So tell me what happened...

603
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:22,970
..during the night.

604
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:25,330
You were there. You saw the nights.

605
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:27,012
You know, just... it was black.

606
00:35:27,100 --> 00:35:28,249
Just... black.

607
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:30,296
Tell me what happened that night.

608
00:35:31,860 --> 00:35:33,976
Well, she put us on two-hour watches.

609
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:39,817
Um... it's not like
any of us were going to sleep anyway.

610
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:45,053
(Monfriez)
Head down, Altameyer. You might lose it.

611
00:35:46,860 --> 00:35:47,815
You OK, Captain?

612
00:35:47,900 --> 00:35:49,811
Shit in my eye.

613
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:51,652
Will our guys come tonight?

614
00:35:51,780 --> 00:35:53,099
They'll be here.

615
00:35:53,180 --> 00:35:54,693
Dust is blowing pretty bad.

616
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:57,055
l don't know
how much longer Rady can hang on.

617
00:35:57,140 --> 00:35:59,449
l can hear the ragheads
when you're not gabbing.

618
00:35:59,540 --> 00:36:01,417
Then l'd suggest everybody just...

619
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:23,013
They're going away.

620
00:36:23,100 --> 00:36:24,613
lt was just a probe.

621
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:25,735
llario?

622
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:26,730
l'm OK.

623
00:36:26,820 --> 00:36:27,730
Altameyer?

624
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:28,570
My ear!

625
00:36:28,660 --> 00:36:29,615
Monfriez?

626
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:31,258
l... l took one.

627
00:36:31,340 --> 00:36:36,130
- Rady?
- Hanging in. How about you, Cap?

628
00:36:36,540 --> 00:36:37,495
Unh...

629
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:39,377
Oh, shit.

630
00:36:39,460 --> 00:36:41,098
Stay with Rady.

631
00:36:47,060 --> 00:36:48,652
l like to come here.

632
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:52,653
lt's notjust the bikinis,
although they ain't bad.

633
00:36:52,740 --> 00:36:55,254
lt's these kids.

634
00:36:55,340 --> 00:36:57,092
l like to watch them, you know?

635
00:36:57,180 --> 00:37:00,058
My folks had this place
out on Calaveras Lake.

636
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:03,098
l still go there sometimes, watch 'em dive.

637
00:37:03,180 --> 00:37:04,659
They do the damnedest things.

638
00:37:04,740 --> 00:37:07,095
They never think about the consequences.

639
00:37:08,980 --> 00:37:10,379
lmagine that.

640
00:37:10,460 --> 00:37:13,497
lmagine not thinking
about the consequences?

641
00:37:13,580 --> 00:37:15,252
lmagine that.

642
00:37:19,220 --> 00:37:21,051
Are... are we done?

643
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:26,095
After the attack...

644
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:27,977
..during the night...

645
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:29,937
What?

646
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:31,453
l mean, we waited.

647
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:32,893
l... l still don't...

648
00:37:32,980 --> 00:37:37,531
- l... l don't know what you...
- Just go on with what happened.

649
00:37:40,980 --> 00:37:46,737
Well, Karen,...
the captain,... uh, was hurt pretty bad.

650
00:37:47,940 --> 00:37:49,168
Ohh...

651
00:37:49,260 --> 00:37:52,297
Unh...

652
00:37:52,380 --> 00:37:54,257
Unh!

653
00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:56,579
How many rounds left?

654
00:37:56,660 --> 00:37:57,888
Just a sec.

655
00:37:57,980 --> 00:37:59,333
How many rounds?

656
00:37:59,420 --> 00:38:01,251
l just opened my last can of ammo.

657
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:03,331
Five mags for the M-16,...

658
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:04,455
..9-mil's full.

659
00:38:04,660 --> 00:38:05,536
Mine's empty.

660
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:08,818
Fire a couple of rounds off.

661
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:11,812
- Let 'em know we're still alive.
- Roger that, Captain.

662
00:38:13,620 --> 00:38:17,090
Now save your ammo
for something you can see.

663
00:38:19,220 --> 00:38:23,418
During the course of the incident,
did she display any doubt, any fear...

664
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:26,810
..when she had to make
these life-and-death decisions?

665
00:38:26,900 --> 00:38:28,652
No.

666
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:30,014
No. Never.

667
00:38:30,100 --> 00:38:31,249
She just made 'em.

668
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:33,217
Just like that?

669
00:38:33,300 --> 00:38:34,733
Just like that.

670
00:38:34,820 --> 00:38:37,573
Karen,... the captain... she had this quality.

671
00:38:37,660 --> 00:38:40,174
The heavier the pressure,
the calmer she got.

672
00:38:40,260 --> 00:38:42,012
We knew they were out there,...

673
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:43,692
..sneaking up on us.

674
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:47,295
But we also knew
at first light they were going to attack.

675
00:38:47,380 --> 00:38:51,214
l don't know why people think only
good things happen when the sun rises.

676
00:38:51,460 --> 00:38:52,529
lncoming!

677
00:39:02,540 --> 00:39:03,495
How many?

678
00:39:03,580 --> 00:39:04,808
100. Maybe more.

679
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:06,379
Any good at hand-to-hand?

680
00:39:06,460 --> 00:39:08,655
Wait till they get closer.

681
00:39:08,740 --> 00:39:11,254
Make every round count!

682
00:39:14,260 --> 00:39:15,739
- Shit!
- Quiet!

683
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,299
What in Christ for?

684
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:18,813
They know we're here!

685
00:39:18,900 --> 00:39:20,777
Quiet! l hear something!

686
00:39:20,860 --> 00:39:21,849
(helicopter)

687
00:39:24,100 --> 00:39:25,931
Choppers!

688
00:39:28,340 --> 00:39:30,570
Hey!

689
00:39:30,660 --> 00:39:33,379
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

690
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:35,052
Go! Go!

691
00:39:35,140 --> 00:39:36,368
Yeah! (laughs)

692
00:39:45,220 --> 00:39:46,539
Let's get out of here!

693
00:39:46,620 --> 00:39:47,609
llario, get the captain!

694
00:39:47,700 --> 00:39:49,053
There's the rescue!

695
00:39:56,420 --> 00:39:58,570
Help Rady!

696
00:39:58,660 --> 00:40:00,218
Pick him up!

697
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:01,972
Go! Let's go! Let go! Let's go!

698
00:40:03,540 --> 00:40:05,895
Come on! Let's move! Move it!

699
00:40:06,980 --> 00:40:08,379
Gotta go! We gotta go!

700
00:40:08,460 --> 00:40:10,496
Come back for me with a stretcher!

701
00:40:10,580 --> 00:40:11,615
Go!

702
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:33,530
llario, let's get the fuck outta here!

703
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:37,011
Get the fuck outta here!

704
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:51,253
Aah!

705
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:52,819
Aah!

706
00:40:55,180 --> 00:40:56,169
Medic!

707
00:40:58,220 --> 00:40:59,972
Come on! Get him up!

708
00:41:03,780 --> 00:41:05,816
Move! Come on! Let's go!

709
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:10,535
Where's Walden?

710
00:41:11,820 --> 00:41:13,333
Captain Walden is dead.

711
00:41:16,780 --> 00:41:19,374
Strike leader, this is Dustoff-6.

712
00:41:19,460 --> 00:41:22,418
We have all the friendlies.
You're clear and hot.

713
00:41:22,500 --> 00:41:25,060
Roger, Dustoff-6. Going on down.

714
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:35,731
So...

715
00:41:35,820 --> 00:41:38,175
ls she gonna get it?
ls she gonna get the medal?

716
00:41:38,260 --> 00:41:41,616
Well, l sincerely hope so.

717
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:45,056
l just... l don't want to tell that story again.

718
00:41:45,140 --> 00:41:47,256
Not one more time.

719
00:41:47,340 --> 00:41:48,932
Yeah, l understand.

720
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:52,059
May l be excused?

721
00:41:52,140 --> 00:41:54,176
Yes, you can.

722
00:41:54,260 --> 00:41:57,093
Oh, one more thing l'm confused about.

723
00:41:58,540 --> 00:42:00,053
This M-16...

724
00:42:01,340 --> 00:42:02,250
What?

725
00:42:02,340 --> 00:42:04,137
Did it run out of ammo?

726
00:42:05,820 --> 00:42:07,697
Uh, what did l say?

727
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:11,653
l don't remember. That's why l'm asking.

728
00:42:13,140 --> 00:42:14,778
l guess, uh...

729
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:18,694
l guess it ran out of ammo
some time during the morning.

730
00:42:18,780 --> 00:42:20,532
Um...

731
00:42:20,620 --> 00:42:22,212
Or, no, some time during the night...

732
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:23,619
l don't know.

733
00:42:23,700 --> 00:42:26,897
See, the Blackhawk crew
said they heard M-16 fire...

734
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:30,131
..during the rescue that morning.

735
00:42:30,420 --> 00:42:32,092
Did they?

736
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:34,569
That's right.

737
00:42:34,660 --> 00:42:36,252
Must've been wrong, then.

738
00:42:36,340 --> 00:42:37,250
Them or you?

739
00:42:37,340 --> 00:42:38,739
Who, them or you?

740
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:40,048
Oh, them. Them, yeah.

741
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,698
No, they must have been wrong.

742
00:42:41,940 --> 00:42:43,658
OK.

743
00:42:44,740 --> 00:42:45,729
OK.

744
00:42:47,420 --> 00:42:48,853
What about the letter?

745
00:42:50,260 --> 00:42:51,170
A what?

746
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:55,174
You and Walden traded letters to send home
in case anything happened to you.

747
00:42:55,260 --> 00:42:56,329
Oh, yeah. Yes, sir.

748
00:42:56,420 --> 00:42:57,694
So, who was hers to?

749
00:42:57,780 --> 00:42:58,690
Her folks.

750
00:42:58,780 --> 00:43:01,169
- So you sent it?
- Yeah.

751
00:43:01,260 --> 00:43:02,898
Her folks, they're good people.

752
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:04,811
They got a farm out in Abilene.

753
00:43:04,900 --> 00:43:08,734
They'd come to Hood, look after her kid
while we went out on exercises.

754
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:11,095
Yeah... Yeah.

755
00:43:12,860 --> 00:43:13,770
OK.

756
00:43:13,860 --> 00:43:15,578
Thank you, Specialist.

757
00:43:15,660 --> 00:43:17,059
Thank you very much, sir.

758
00:43:22,780 --> 00:43:24,657
l read somewhere...

759
00:43:24,740 --> 00:43:27,857
..that if a child doesn't see a person die,...

760
00:43:27,940 --> 00:43:30,898
..or dead, like in a casket,...

761
00:43:30,980 --> 00:43:33,972
..that the person isn't really dead for them.

762
00:43:35,140 --> 00:43:36,858
That'd be nice, wouldn't it?

763
00:43:38,140 --> 00:43:39,129
Yes, ma'am.

764
00:43:41,060 --> 00:43:44,257
lt was, uh... unusual, wasn't it,...

765
00:43:44,340 --> 00:43:46,900
..for Karen to want to be a helicopter pilot?

766
00:43:46,980 --> 00:43:49,096
l guess that's my fault.

767
00:43:49,180 --> 00:43:51,410
l took her to the fair when she was 11.

768
00:43:51,500 --> 00:43:54,651
12 - 7th grade.

769
00:43:54,740 --> 00:43:57,413
Anyway, there was a helicopter there.

770
00:43:57,500 --> 00:43:59,491
Small one with a bubble up front.

771
00:43:59,580 --> 00:44:02,048
The fella... the pilot was selling rides.

772
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:04,734
l bought Karen a ticket.

773
00:44:04,820 --> 00:44:06,856
lt was a short ride.

774
00:44:06,940 --> 00:44:09,500
But when she came down...

775
00:44:09,580 --> 00:44:12,378
Well, l don't think
she ever came down, actually.

776
00:44:13,140 --> 00:44:17,691
She showed up
at the dinner table one day,...

777
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:20,613
..just after she finished TCU.

778
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:22,531
She's joined the Army.

779
00:44:22,620 --> 00:44:24,372
She wants to fly helicopters.

780
00:44:24,460 --> 00:44:25,973
She's real stubborn about it, too.

781
00:44:26,060 --> 00:44:28,016
That's our Karen, you know, stubborn.

782
00:44:28,100 --> 00:44:29,897
So's Anne Marie here.

783
00:44:32,380 --> 00:44:34,291
Come here, honey.

784
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:35,335
Excuse me.

785
00:44:42,020 --> 00:44:43,499
Uh, the young men,...

786
00:44:43,580 --> 00:44:47,289
..the ones that came to tell us about Karen...

787
00:44:47,380 --> 00:44:49,848
..they were dressed just like you.

788
00:44:49,940 --> 00:44:52,613
Oh, l see.

789
00:44:52,700 --> 00:44:53,769
Major Teegarden,...

790
00:44:53,860 --> 00:44:58,251
..her commanding officer, he came, too,
when he came back from the Gulf.

791
00:44:58,740 --> 00:45:01,891
Brought this photo back for Anne Marie.

792
00:45:03,340 --> 00:45:05,171
Meant a lot to us...

793
00:45:05,260 --> 00:45:07,137
..him coming to see us,...

794
00:45:07,220 --> 00:45:09,893
..telling us in person how Karen died.

795
00:45:09,980 --> 00:45:12,858
l lost men over there, too.

796
00:45:12,940 --> 00:45:14,373
l spoke to the major.

797
00:45:14,460 --> 00:45:19,329
Everybody thought the world
of your daughter. So did Specialist llario.

798
00:45:20,860 --> 00:45:23,055
lt would sure help if l could see her letter.

799
00:45:23,140 --> 00:45:24,971
l mean, if it's not too private.

800
00:45:25,060 --> 00:45:26,015
Letter?

801
00:45:26,100 --> 00:45:28,250
From llario?

802
00:45:29,900 --> 00:45:32,698
l'll check my notes. Must be my mistake.

803
00:45:32,780 --> 00:45:34,452
This her husband here?

804
00:45:34,540 --> 00:45:37,373
No. That's Karen's older brother Billy.

805
00:45:37,460 --> 00:45:39,928
Her husband's up in Michigan.

806
00:45:41,420 --> 00:45:44,457
He and Karen divorced
after only a year or so.

807
00:45:44,540 --> 00:45:49,409
He never... well,... it was no picnic.

808
00:45:49,500 --> 00:45:51,411
Karen raised Anne Marie on her own.

809
00:45:51,500 --> 00:45:55,129
We'd have been thrilled
to have Anne Marie with us all the time,...

810
00:45:55,220 --> 00:45:58,496
..what with the Army and all.

811
00:45:58,580 --> 00:46:00,491
But Karen was a real good mom.

812
00:46:01,620 --> 00:46:05,249
Never asked for help
unless she really needed it.

813
00:46:05,340 --> 00:46:08,093
You can't imagine how hard it was for her...

814
00:46:08,180 --> 00:46:11,490
..to go off and leave that little girl
to fight in a war,...

815
00:46:11,580 --> 00:46:14,777
..but it was important to Karen
to do her duty.

816
00:46:14,860 --> 00:46:16,418
So she went.

817
00:46:18,180 --> 00:46:20,091
(children's voices)

818
00:46:40,860 --> 00:46:43,772
You've been out here 20 minutes
since l spotted you.

819
00:46:43,860 --> 00:46:46,420
- How much longer before that?
- 15.

820
00:46:49,820 --> 00:46:52,288
l see you, uh...

821
00:46:52,380 --> 00:46:54,132
..got the new refrigerator.

822
00:46:54,220 --> 00:46:58,611
Do you think the kids will understand
why their daddy is out here in a Chevy...

823
00:46:58,700 --> 00:47:01,692
..instead of playing with them
in the front yard?

824
00:47:01,780 --> 00:47:04,374
Or at Fort Hood,
like you told me you were?

825
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:07,614
Are you back?

826
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:10,099
l'm in transit.

827
00:47:19,660 --> 00:47:22,049
You know, Nat, it took me a long time...

828
00:47:22,140 --> 00:47:25,815
..to figure out how to be an Army wife
without obliterating myself.

829
00:47:25,900 --> 00:47:27,777
lt wasn't easy, but l did it.

830
00:47:27,860 --> 00:47:29,851
l know you did, Mer.

831
00:47:30,860 --> 00:47:32,896
So it wouldn't be a hardship for me...

832
00:47:32,980 --> 00:47:35,369
..to learn how not to be an Army wife...

833
00:47:35,460 --> 00:47:37,655
..if my husband wasn't in the Army any more.

834
00:47:37,740 --> 00:47:40,015
The Army's my life, Mer.

835
00:47:41,140 --> 00:47:42,732
And so are we.

836
00:47:45,620 --> 00:47:47,895
You don't have to figure it all out, Nat.

837
00:47:47,980 --> 00:47:51,336
You just have to admit that you can't.

838
00:47:53,020 --> 00:47:55,454
You have to want to be here with us,...

839
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:56,529
..that's all.

840
00:47:59,420 --> 00:48:01,172
We'll be here.

841
00:48:04,260 --> 00:48:05,579
For a while.

842
00:48:16,900 --> 00:48:18,049
Now go away.

843
00:48:18,740 --> 00:48:21,937
lf you're not going to stay,
l don't want the kids to see you.

844
00:48:28,340 --> 00:48:30,900
- (tape) This M-16, did it run out of ammo?
- (buzzer)

845
00:48:30,980 --> 00:48:32,811
(woman) Yes, sir?

846
00:48:32,900 --> 00:48:36,813
- Colonel Serling, you can go in now.
- l don't remember...

847
00:48:42,300 --> 00:48:43,813
Hey, Nat, what's up?

848
00:48:43,900 --> 00:48:45,253
General.

849
00:48:45,340 --> 00:48:48,776
lt's the Walden file, sir.
One or two discrepancies.

850
00:48:48,860 --> 00:48:49,815
Discrepancies?

851
00:48:49,900 --> 00:48:50,969
Yes, sir.

852
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:53,938
l knew those White House clowns
were up to something.

853
00:48:54,020 --> 00:48:57,251
- lf she doesn't deserve it, she won't get it.
- lt's not Captain Walden, sir.

854
00:48:57,340 --> 00:49:00,889
lt's some of the details of the stories
l'm getting from her crew.

855
00:49:00,980 --> 00:49:04,336
- l don't know how significant...
- l'm drowning in paper here.

856
00:49:04,420 --> 00:49:07,218
They're crawling all over my ass
for combat assessments,...

857
00:49:07,300 --> 00:49:12,328
Sir, l just wanted to let you know this is
not a rubber-stamp situation, that's all.

858
00:49:12,420 --> 00:49:16,777
Now, this specialist, uh, llario,
there's something funny about his story.

859
00:49:16,860 --> 00:49:20,250
We're not giving the medal to llario.
We're giving it to Walden.

860
00:49:20,340 --> 00:49:21,295
Roger.

861
00:49:21,380 --> 00:49:22,733
Splendid. Move forward.

862
00:49:22,820 --> 00:49:26,813
OK. The discrepancies specifically
relate to... use of an M-16 rifle...

863
00:49:26,900 --> 00:49:30,415
Come on, Nat! No two eyewitnesses
ever agree on every detail.

864
00:49:30,500 --> 00:49:32,411
You know that as well as l do.

865
00:49:32,500 --> 00:49:34,172
When do we get that report?

866
00:49:34,260 --> 00:49:36,091
l want the White House off my back.

867
00:49:36,180 --> 00:49:37,499
A few days, sir.

868
00:49:37,580 --> 00:49:42,210
You agree that this report should be
as detailed and accurate as possible?

869
00:49:42,580 --> 00:49:44,536
Which means exactly what, Colonel?

870
00:49:44,620 --> 00:49:47,930
Which means exactly what l said, sir.

871
00:49:48,020 --> 00:49:48,975
(knock on door)

872
00:49:50,140 --> 00:49:54,531
Sorry, sir. This is the second copy
of Colonel Serling's Al Bathra deposition.

873
00:49:54,620 --> 00:49:57,930
The investigator seemed to have
misplaced the last one.

874
00:49:58,020 --> 00:49:59,419
Rise above.

875
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:01,058
This will all be over soon.

876
00:50:02,620 --> 00:50:05,373
Will there be
a public statement of the facts...

877
00:50:05,460 --> 00:50:07,257
..when the investigation is over, sir?

878
00:50:07,340 --> 00:50:11,538
There's been a decision not to release
any findings until every case...

879
00:50:11,620 --> 00:50:13,451
..has been thoroughly reviewed.

880
00:50:13,540 --> 00:50:16,452
Well, how long do you imagine
that will be, sir?

881
00:50:16,540 --> 00:50:22,251
l mean, next time l see Lieutenant Boylar's
parents, l'd like to tell them the whole truth.

882
00:50:22,340 --> 00:50:26,697
You know how many grieving parents
l had to deal with during Vietnam?

883
00:50:26,780 --> 00:50:27,769
This is not Vietnam.

884
00:50:27,860 --> 00:50:30,977
Lieutenant Boylar's tank
was hit by uranium-depleted shells.

885
00:50:31,060 --> 00:50:34,370
We're the only country
in the world that uses them.

886
00:50:34,460 --> 00:50:38,339
We got reporters from the Washington Post
looking for the truth,...

887
00:50:38,420 --> 00:50:40,854
..and the only person that knows it
can't say it...

888
00:50:40,940 --> 00:50:44,774
..because these investigators
are dragging their backsides!

889
00:50:44,860 --> 00:50:48,933
Someone has got to be
accountable for this,... sir.

890
00:50:58,780 --> 00:51:00,099
Take a seat.

891
00:51:11,740 --> 00:51:15,255
Nat, l'm going to give you
all the rope in the world.

892
00:51:15,340 --> 00:51:17,490
First you imply l'm not interested...

893
00:51:17,580 --> 00:51:19,775
..in an accurate report on Captain Walden.

894
00:51:19,860 --> 00:51:23,933
Now you're suggesting there must be
some cover-up going on about Al Bathra.

895
00:51:24,020 --> 00:51:25,851
So how do you want me to respond?

896
00:51:25,940 --> 00:51:27,817
As your commanding officer,...

897
00:51:27,900 --> 00:51:31,734
..or as your friend
who nursed you, pushed promotions,...

898
00:51:31,820 --> 00:51:35,051
..and fucking burped your kids
at their baptisms?

899
00:51:36,460 --> 00:51:38,416
Just how should l respond?

900
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:41,299
l'm sorry, sir.

901
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:44,570
l should hope by God you would be.

902
00:51:45,500 --> 00:51:47,092
Now,...

903
00:51:47,180 --> 00:51:50,855
..losing a man like your friend Boylar,...

904
00:51:52,020 --> 00:51:53,294
..l've been there.

905
00:51:54,780 --> 00:51:55,769
Well, this...

906
00:51:55,860 --> 00:51:57,691
..whole mess...

907
00:51:59,220 --> 00:52:01,859
lt's my ass on the line
right there beside yours.

908
00:52:01,940 --> 00:52:05,376
l can feel the chill in the air
as well as you can.

909
00:52:05,460 --> 00:52:07,257
Yes, sir.

910
00:52:07,340 --> 00:52:09,774
And l know about the drinking.

911
00:52:09,940 --> 00:52:12,818
And if l have to write you up,...

912
00:52:12,900 --> 00:52:15,368
..it'll just be one more bite out of your record.

913
00:52:15,460 --> 00:52:16,609
Clean it up.

914
00:52:16,700 --> 00:52:19,089
Get yourself in a programme.

915
00:52:19,180 --> 00:52:20,977
l'll be looking for that report.

916
00:52:21,060 --> 00:52:22,539
Soon.

917
00:52:36,740 --> 00:52:40,289
- (Nat) Yes, this is the Serling residence.
- (Mer) We're not in right now...

918
00:52:40,380 --> 00:52:45,090
- But at the tone, leave a message and...
- (kids) We'll call you when we get home.

919
00:52:45,180 --> 00:52:46,659
(laughter)

920
00:52:46,740 --> 00:52:48,139
(beep)

921
00:53:06,860 --> 00:53:07,736
(gunfire)

922
00:53:07,820 --> 00:53:09,458
You better get your head into this!

923
00:53:09,540 --> 00:53:13,215
l'm going to drop you
from this programme like a hot rock!

924
00:53:13,300 --> 00:53:14,779
You better hurry up!

925
00:53:16,420 --> 00:53:19,412
Morning, sir. Monfriez is over there.
l'll get him for you.

926
00:53:19,500 --> 00:53:20,410
Thank you.

927
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:23,731
What the fuck are you doing, soldier?
Where are your men?

928
00:53:23,820 --> 00:53:26,095
- There, sir.
- Yeah? What do you call that?

929
00:53:26,180 --> 00:53:27,772
You see that man?

930
00:53:27,860 --> 00:53:31,250
You and he are brothers.
He depends on you. You depend on him.

931
00:53:31,340 --> 00:53:33,649
You never leave a man behind.

932
00:53:33,740 --> 00:53:36,937
- Yes, Drill Sergeant!
- Now get the fuck out of here.

933
00:53:37,500 --> 00:53:38,500
(Nat) You were in Panama?

934
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:40,000
Yes, sir.

935
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:41,500
Were you there, sir?